  <name>Loopa</name>
  <summary>Phase space simulator for complex dynamical systems</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      Loopa is a phase space simulator for visualizing and analyzing complex dynamical systems.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Built-in models for the Lorenz Attractor, Chua's Circuit, Duffing and Van der Pol Oscillators, Lotka-Volterra equations, RLC Circuits, and mechanical systems</li>
      <li>Numerical integration using Runge-Kutta methods</li>
      <li>Phase space visualization of system trajectories, attractors, and chaotic behaviors</li>
      <li>Poincaré sections for analysis of periodic and chaotic orbits</li>
      <li>Configurable system parameters to observe mathematical bifurcations</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <developer id="rs.ilijaruzic">
